\i0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs32 \cf0 In this paper we have sought to formalize the notion of a deleveraging crisis, in which there is an abrupt downward revision of views about how much debt it is safe for individual agents to have, and in which this revision of views forces highly indebted agents to reduce their spending sharply. Such a sudden shift to deleveraging can, if it is large enough, create major problems of 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl200\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs16 \cf0 \up13 14 
\fs26 \up0 As it makes people work more due to an increase in the marginal utility of private consumption. 
\fs30 24 
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
\cf0 {{\NeXTGraphic page3image17040.png \width2440 \height16
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
